"{\"uid\": \"mondaq.com-unitedstates-patent-1502890-olympic-thrills-to-patent-skills-understanding-apparatus-and-method-claims\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"This year's Olympic Games have already been packed with compelling storylines.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 79, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This year's Olympic Games\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 25}, {\"ngram\": \"compelling storylines\", \"from\": 56, \"to\": 77}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These storylines include the somewhat controversial opening ceremony to Yusuf \\\"hold my beer\\\" Dikec winning hearts and the silver medal in pistol shooting, and Simone Biles clinching her tenth gold medal (with more possibly on the way).\", \"from\": 80, \"to\": 319, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These storylines\", \"from\": 80, \"to\": 96}, {\"ngram\": \"the somewhat controversial opening ceremony\", \"from\": 105, \"to\": 148}, {\"ngram\": \"Yusuf\", \"from\": 152, \"to\": 157}, {\"ngram\": \"my beer\", \"from\": 164, \"to\": 171}, {\"ngram\": \"Dikec\", \"from\": 173, \"to\": 178}, {\"ngram\": \"hearts\", \"from\": 187, \"to\": 193}, {\"ngram\": \"the silver medal\", \"from\": 198, \"to\": 214}, {\"ngram\": \"pistol shooting\", \"from\": 218, \"to\": 233}, {\"ngram\": \"Simone Biles\", \"from\": 239, \"to\": 251}, {\"ngram\": \"her tenth gold medal\", \"from\": 262, \"to\": 282}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 306, \"to\": 313}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adding to the Olympic headlines, on August 4, USA's Noah Lyles added to the Olympic headlines by edging past Kishane Thompson, from Jamaica, to win his first Olympic gold medal with a lifetime best of 9.784 seconds, just 0.005 seconds ahead of Thompson's 9.789.\", \"from\": 320, \"to\": 585, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 366, \"end\": 369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999074671039, \"rank\": 9.244289944029439e-08, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 373, \"end\": 383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 454, \"end\": 461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999999905194272, \"rank\": 7.817527733296368e-09, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic headlines\", \"from\": 330, \"to\": 351}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 356, \"to\": 362}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic headlines\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 413}, {\"ngram\": \"Kishane Thompson\", \"from\": 429, \"to\": 445}, {\"ngram\": \"his first Olympic gold medal\", \"from\": 468, \"to\": 496}, {\"ngram\": \"a lifetime\", \"from\": 502, \"to\": 512}, {\"ngram\": \"9.784 seconds\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 534}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The result was not clear until nearly a full minute after crossing the finish line, as the competitors waited nervously for the photo finish details.\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 737, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The result\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 596}, {\"ngram\": \"nearly a full minute\", \"from\": 617, \"to\": 637}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish line\", \"from\": 653, \"to\": 668}, {\"ngram\": \"the competitors\", \"from\": 673, \"to\": 688}, {\"ngram\": \"the photo finish details\", \"from\": 710, \"to\": 734}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The photo finish finds its origins in horse racing.\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 790, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The photo finish\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 755}, {\"ngram\": \"its origins\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 773}, {\"ngram\": \"horse racing\", \"from\": 777, \"to\": 789}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before the advent of photography, close races were judged by three stewards stationed at the finish line, often resulting in disputes and controversy.\", \"from\": 791, \"to\": 944, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the advent\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 808}, {\"ngram\": \"photography\", \"from\": 812, \"to\": 823}, {\"ngram\": \"close races\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 836}, {\"ngram\": \"three stewards\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 866}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish line\", \"from\": 880, \"to\": 895}, {\"ngram\": \"disputes\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 924}, {\"ngram\": \"controversy\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 940}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As horse racing and betting became more popular in the early 20th century, the need for a more precise method to determine race outcomes grew.\", \"from\": 945, \"to\": 1089, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"horse\", \"from\": 948, \"to\": 953}, {\"ngram\": \"the early 20th century\", \"from\": 996, \"to\": 1018}, {\"ngram\": \"a more precise method\", \"from\": 1033, \"to\": 1054}, {\"ngram\": \"race outcomes\", \"from\": 1068, \"to\": 1081}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The earliest known racetrack photo finish images were captured in 1890 by John Charles Hemment, a pioneer in action photography.\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1220, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1171, \"end\": 1178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\", \"score\": 0.6976092517475236, \"rank\": 0.43337519550739617, \"text\": \"Charles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The earliest known racetrack photo finish images\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1139}, {\"ngram\": \"a pioneer\", \"from\": 1187, \"to\": 1196}, {\"ngram\": \"action photography\", \"from\": 1200, \"to\": 1218}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hemment's method involved a horse breaking a thin thread at the finish line, triggering the camera's shutter.\", \"from\": 1222, \"to\": 1332, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hemment's method\", \"from\": 1222, \"to\": 1238}, {\"ngram\": \"a horse\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1255}, {\"ngram\": \"a thin thread\", \"from\": 1265, \"to\": 1278}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish line\", \"from\": 1282, \"to\": 1297}, {\"ngram\": \"the camera's shutter\", \"from\": 1310, \"to\": 1330}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This technique was far from perfect, as it often failed to capture the exact finish line moment and could not record the positions of other horses.\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1483, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This technique\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1347}, {\"ngram\": \"the exact finish line moment\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1428}, {\"ngram\": \"the positions\", \"from\": 1450, \"to\": 1463}, {\"ngram\": \"other horses\", \"from\": 1467, \"to\": 1479}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the 1920s, motion picture cameras began to record races, but their low frame rates made it difficult to determine the exact moment horses crossed the finish line.\", \"from\": 1485, \"to\": 1652, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"motion picture cameras\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1521}, {\"ngram\": \"races\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1543}, {\"ngram\": \"their low frame rates\", \"from\": 1549, \"to\": 1570}, {\"ngram\": \"the exact moment horses\", \"from\": 1602, \"to\": 1625}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish line\", \"from\": 1634, \"to\": 1649}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The breakthrough came in 1937 when Hollywood icon Bing Crosby opened the Del Mar Thoroughbred Club and enlisted Paramount Pictures engineer Lorenzo Del Riccio to develop a better solution.\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1844, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1689, \"end\": 1698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999963700231492, \"rank\": 3.629990163301257e-06, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1709, \"end\": 1715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bing_Crosby\", \"score\": 0.9999999999845386, \"rank\": 1.566052873269396e-11, \"text\": \"Crosby\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bing_Crosby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bing_Crosby\"}, {\"begin\": 1736, \"end\": 1748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thoroughbred\", \"score\": 0.9999910105838588, \"rank\": 8.989408007809613e-06, \"text\": \"Thoroughbred\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thoroughbred\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thoroughbred\"}, {\"begin\": 1767, \"end\": 1785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paramount_Pictures\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.051407929829876e-22, \"text\": \"Paramount Pictures\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paramount_Pictures\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paramount_Pictures\"}, {\"begin\": 1795, \"end\": 1802, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lorenzo_de'_Medici\", \"score\": 0.9998646882995929, \"rank\": 0.00013533001211778341, \"text\": \"Lorenzo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lorenzo_de'_Medici\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lorenzo_de'_Medici\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The breakthrough\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1669}, {\"ngram\": \"a better solution\", \"from\": 1823, \"to\": 1840}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Del Riccio's circular flow camera, first used on Del Mar's opening day, revolutionized finish line photography for horse racing and other sports.\", \"from\": 1845, \"to\": 1993, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Del Riccio's circular flow camera\", \"from\": 1845, \"to\": 1878}, {\"ngram\": \"Del Mar's opening day\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 1915}, {\"ngram\": \"finish line photography\", \"from\": 1932, \"to\": 1955}, {\"ngram\": \"horse racing\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 1972}, {\"ngram\": \"other sports\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 1989}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His camera quickly became popular, with race tracks across the country eager to purchase it.\", \"from\": 1994, \"to\": 2087, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His camera\", \"from\": 1994, \"to\": 2004}, {\"ngram\": \"race tracks\", \"from\": 2034, \"to\": 2045}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 2053, \"to\": 2064}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Del Riccio's camera had a unique design featuring a thin, vertical slit that limited its field of vision to a four-inch slice.\", \"from\": 2089, \"to\": 2217, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Del Riccio's camera\", \"from\": 2089, \"to\": 2108}, {\"ngram\": \"a unique design\", \"from\": 2113, \"to\": 2128}, {\"ngram\": \"a thin, vertical slit\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2160}, {\"ngram\": \"its field\", \"from\": 2174, \"to\": 2183}, {\"ngram\": \"vision\", \"from\": 2187, \"to\": 2193}, {\"ngram\": \"a four-inch slice\", \"from\": 2197, \"to\": 2214}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Positioned above the track and aligned with the finish line, the camera recorded as strip film moved across the slit at the same speed as the horses, capturing them from nose to tail.\", \"from\": 2218, \"to\": 2403, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 2235, \"to\": 2244}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish line\", \"from\": 2262, \"to\": 2277}, {\"ngram\": \"the camera\", \"from\": 2279, \"to\": 2289}, {\"ngram\": \"strip film\", \"from\": 2302, \"to\": 2312}, {\"ngram\": \"the slit\", \"from\": 2326, \"to\": 2334}, {\"ngram\": \"the same speed\", \"from\": 2338, \"to\": 2352}, {\"ngram\": \"the horses\", \"from\": 2356, \"to\": 2366}, {\"ngram\": \"nose\", \"from\": 2388, \"to\": 2392}, {\"ngram\": \"tail\", \"from\": 2396, \"to\": 2400}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This continuous motion resulted in distorted horse lengths but accurately depicted the order of finishes.\", \"from\": 2404, \"to\": 2511, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This continuous motion\", \"from\": 2404, \"to\": 2426}, {\"ngram\": \"distorted horse lengths\", \"from\": 2439, \"to\": 2462}, {\"ngram\": \"the order\", \"from\": 2487, \"to\": 2496}, {\"ngram\": \"finishes\", \"from\": 2500, \"to\": 2508}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Del Riccio set about to solve the problem through the use of a tapered or angular slit, known as the V-slit.\", \"from\": 2513, \"to\": 2622, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Del Riccio\", \"from\": 2513, \"to\": 2523}, {\"ngram\": \"the problem\", \"from\": 2543, \"to\": 2554}, {\"ngram\": \"the use\", \"from\": 2563, \"to\": 2570}, {\"ngram\": \"a tapered or angular slit\", \"from\": 2574, \"to\": 2599}, {\"ngram\": \"the V-slit\", \"from\": 2610, \"to\": 2620}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In March 1939, Del Riccio filed a patent application for this new camera.\", \"from\": 2623, \"to\": 2697, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"March\", \"from\": 2626, \"to\": 2631}, {\"ngram\": \"Del Riccio\", \"from\": 2638, \"to\": 2648}, {\"ngram\": \"a patent application\", \"from\": 2655, \"to\": 2675}, {\"ngram\": \"this new camera\", \"from\": 2680, \"to\": 2695}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The inventions associated with this new technology issued as U.S. Patent Nos.2,320,350and2,382,617.\", \"from\": 2698, \"to\": 2799, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2773, \"end\": 2776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nitrous_oxide\", \"score\": 0.9996444245750749, \"rank\": 0.00035570187639923946, \"text\": \"Nos\", \"types\": [\"Q11173\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nitrous_oxide\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nitrous_oxide\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The inventions\", \"from\": 2698, \"to\": 2712}, {\"ngram\": \"this new technology\", \"from\": 2729, \"to\": 2748}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The '350 patent is directed to a camera (i.e., an apparatus claim), while the '617 patent is directed to a method of making a photographic record.\", \"from\": 2800, \"to\": 2948, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The '350 patent\", \"from\": 2800, \"to\": 2815}, {\"ngram\": \"a camera\", \"from\": 2831, \"to\": 2839}, {\"ngram\": \"an apparatus\", \"from\": 2847, \"to\": 2859}, {\"ngram\": \"the '617 patent\", \"from\": 2874, \"to\": 2889}, {\"ngram\": \"a method\", \"from\": 2905, \"to\": 2913}, {\"ngram\": \"a photographic record\", \"from\": 2924, \"to\": 2945}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the race to secure patent protection, apparatus claims and method claims vie for the gold, each excelling in distinct arenas to champion the inventor's cause.\", \"from\": 2950, \"to\": 3113, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 2953, \"to\": 2961}, {\"ngram\": \"patent protection\", \"from\": 2972, \"to\": 2989}, {\"ngram\": \"apparatus claims\", \"from\": 2991, \"to\": 3007}, {\"ngram\": \"method claims\", \"from\": 3012, \"to\": 3025}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold\", \"from\": 3034, \"to\": 3042}, {\"ngram\": \"distinct arenas\", \"from\": 3062, \"to\": 3077}, {\"ngram\": \"the inventor's cause\", \"from\": 3090, \"to\": 3110}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Apparatus claims, also known as device or product claims, focus on the tangible aspects of an invention.\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3220, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Apparatus claims\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3130}, {\"ngram\": \"device\", \"from\": 3146, \"to\": 3152}, {\"ngram\": \"product claims\", \"from\": 3156, \"to\": 3170}, {\"ngram\": \"the tangible aspects\", \"from\": 3181, \"to\": 3201}, {\"ngram\": \"an invention\", \"from\": 3205, \"to\": 3217}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These claims detail the specific parts and their arrangement within the device, highlighting the configuration and interaction of these components.\", \"from\": 3221, \"to\": 3370, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These claims\", \"from\": 3221, \"to\": 3233}, {\"ngram\": \"the specific parts\", \"from\": 3241, \"to\": 3259}, {\"ngram\": \"their arrangement\", \"from\": 3264, \"to\": 3281}, {\"ngram\": \"the device\", \"from\": 3289, \"to\": 3299}, {\"ngram\": \"the configuration\", \"from\": 3314, \"to\": 3331}, {\"ngram\": \"interaction\", \"from\": 3336, \"to\": 3347}, {\"ngram\": \"these components\", \"from\": 3351, \"to\": 3367}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The scope of protection extends to any device featuring the claimed elements in the described way, ensuring that even if the apparatus is used differently, it can still infringe on the claim if it has the same structure.\", \"from\": 3371, \"to\": 3594, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The scope\", \"from\": 3371, \"to\": 3380}, {\"ngram\": \"protection\", \"from\": 3384, \"to\": 3394}, {\"ngram\": \"any device\", \"from\": 3406, \"to\": 3416}, {\"ngram\": \"the claimed elements\", \"from\": 3427, \"to\": 3447}, {\"ngram\": \"the described way\", \"from\": 3451, \"to\": 3468}, {\"ngram\": \"the apparatus\", \"from\": 3492, \"to\": 3505}, {\"ngram\": \"the claim\", \"from\": 3552, \"to\": 3561}, {\"ngram\": \"the same structure\", \"from\": 3572, \"to\": 3590}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For instance, the apparatus claims of the '350 patent describe the specific parts and the structure of Del Riccio's camera.\", \"from\": 3595, \"to\": 3720, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"instance\", \"from\": 3599, \"to\": 3607}, {\"ngram\": \"the apparatus\", \"from\": 3609, \"to\": 3622}, {\"ngram\": \"the '350 patent\", \"from\": 3633, \"to\": 3648}, {\"ngram\": \"the specific parts\", \"from\": 3658, \"to\": 3676}, {\"ngram\": \"the structure\", \"from\": 3681, \"to\": 3694}, {\"ngram\": \"Del Riccio's camera\", \"from\": 3698, \"to\": 3717}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thus, anyone who manufactures, imports, or sells a camera that reads on each element of the claim would have infringed the '350 patent.\", \"from\": 3721, \"to\": 3859, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 3727, \"to\": 3733}, {\"ngram\": \"imports\", \"from\": 3752, \"to\": 3759}, {\"ngram\": \"a camera\", \"from\": 3770, \"to\": 3778}, {\"ngram\": \"each element\", \"from\": 3793, \"to\": 3805}, {\"ngram\": \"the claim\", \"from\": 3809, \"to\": 3818}, {\"ngram\": \"the '350 patent\", \"from\": 3840, \"to\": 3855}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the other hand, method claims, also known as process claims, resemble a meticulously choreographed Olympic routine, describing a series of steps or actions performed to achieve a specific result.\", \"from\": 3861, \"to\": 4061, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the other hand\", \"from\": 3864, \"to\": 3878}, {\"ngram\": \"method claims\", \"from\": 3880, \"to\": 3893}, {\"ngram\": \"process claims\", \"from\": 3909, \"to\": 3923}, {\"ngram\": \"a meticulously choreographed Olympic routine\", \"from\": 3934, \"to\": 3978}, {\"ngram\": \"a series\", \"from\": 3991, \"to\": 3999}, {\"ngram\": \"steps\", \"from\": 4003, \"to\": 4008}, {\"ngram\": \"actions\", \"from\": 4012, \"to\": 4019}, {\"ngram\": \"a specific result\", \"from\": 4041, \"to\": 4058}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These claims focus on the process rather than the physical components, outlining the individual steps required to perform a task or achieve an outcome.\", \"from\": 4063, \"to\": 4216, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These claims\", \"from\": 4063, \"to\": 4075}, {\"ngram\": \"the process\", \"from\": 4085, \"to\": 4096}, {\"ngram\": \"the physical components\", \"from\": 4109, \"to\": 4132}, {\"ngram\": \"the individual steps\", \"from\": 4144, \"to\": 4164}, {\"ngram\": \"a task\", \"from\": 4185, \"to\": 4191}, {\"ngram\": \"an outcome\", \"from\": 4203, \"to\": 4213}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The protection covers the specific method described, meaning that if someone uses the same process steps, even with different equipment, it could infringe on the method claim.\", \"from\": 4217, \"to\": 4395, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The protection\", \"from\": 4217, \"to\": 4231}, {\"ngram\": \"the specific method\", \"from\": 4239, \"to\": 4258}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 4286, \"to\": 4293}, {\"ngram\": \"the same process steps\", \"from\": 4299, \"to\": 4321}, {\"ngram\": \"different equipment\", \"from\": 4333, \"to\": 4352}, {\"ngram\": \"the method claim\", \"from\": 4375, \"to\": 4391}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, in the '617 patent, the method involves positioning a camera aligned with the finish line, projecting contestant images onto a moving light-sensitive surface at the same speed, and confining the exposure to a narrow strip aligned with the finish line.\", \"from\": 4396, \"to\": 4664, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 4400, \"to\": 4407}, {\"ngram\": \"the '617 patent\", \"from\": 4412, \"to\": 4427}, {\"ngram\": \"the method\", \"from\": 4429, \"to\": 4439}, {\"ngram\": \"a camera\", \"from\": 4461, \"to\": 4469}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish line\", \"from\": 4483, \"to\": 4498}, {\"ngram\": \"contestant images\", \"from\": 4511, \"to\": 4528}, {\"ngram\": \"a moving light-sensitive surface\", \"from\": 4534, \"to\": 4566}, {\"ngram\": \"the same speed\", \"from\": 4570, \"to\": 4584}, {\"ngram\": \"the exposure\", \"from\": 4600, \"to\": 4612}, {\"ngram\": \"a narrow strip\", \"from\": 4616, \"to\": 4630}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish line\", \"from\": 4644, \"to\": 4659}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thus, anyone using these same steps would infringe the '617 patent.\", \"from\": 4665, \"to\": 4733, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 4671, \"to\": 4677}, {\"ngram\": \"these same steps\", \"from\": 4684, \"to\": 4700}, {\"ngram\": \"the '617 patent\", \"from\": 4716, \"to\": 4731}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's important to note that a manufacturer of a product capable of performing these steps would not necessarily infringe the method.\", \"from\": 4734, \"to\": 4868, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a manufacturer\", \"from\": 4762, \"to\": 4776}, {\"ngram\": \"a product\", \"from\": 4780, \"to\": 4789}, {\"ngram\": \"these steps\", \"from\": 4812, \"to\": 4823}, {\"ngram\": \"the method\", \"from\": 4855, \"to\": 4865}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, infringement may occur if the manufacturer provides express instructions that induce a user to perform the method's steps.\", \"from\": 4869, \"to\": 5002, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"infringement\", \"from\": 4878, \"to\": 4890}, {\"ngram\": \"the manufacturer\", \"from\": 4904, \"to\": 4920}, {\"ngram\": \"express instructions\", \"from\": 4930, \"to\": 4950}, {\"ngram\": \"a user\", \"from\": 4963, \"to\": 4969}, {\"ngram\": \"the method's steps\", \"from\": 4981, \"to\": 4999}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The key differences between apparatus and method claims lie in the nature of protection, the criteria for infringement, and their flexibility.\", \"from\": 5004, \"to\": 5148, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The key differences\", \"from\": 5004, \"to\": 5023}, {\"ngram\": \"apparatus\", \"from\": 5032, \"to\": 5041}, {\"ngram\": \"method claims\", \"from\": 5046, \"to\": 5059}, {\"ngram\": \"the nature\", \"from\": 5067, \"to\": 5077}, {\"ngram\": \"protection\", \"from\": 5081, \"to\": 5091}, {\"ngram\": \"the criteria\", \"from\": 5093, \"to\": 5105}, {\"ngram\": \"infringement\", \"from\": 5110, \"to\": 5122}, {\"ngram\": \"their flexibility\", \"from\": 5128, \"to\": 5145}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Apparatus claims protect the physical embodiment of an invention, with infringement occurring if someone makes, uses, sells, or imports a device that includes all the claimed features.\", \"from\": 5149, \"to\": 5335, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Apparatus\", \"from\": 5149, \"to\": 5158}, {\"ngram\": \"the physical embodiment\", \"from\": 5174, \"to\": 5197}, {\"ngram\": \"an invention\", \"from\": 5201, \"to\": 5213}, {\"ngram\": \"infringement\", \"from\": 5220, \"to\": 5232}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 5246, \"to\": 5253}, {\"ngram\": \", uses\", \"from\": 5259, \"to\": 5265}, {\"ngram\": \"sells\", \"from\": 5267, \"to\": 5272}, {\"ngram\": \"a device\", \"from\": 5285, \"to\": 5293}, {\"ngram\": \"all the claimed features\", \"from\": 5308, \"to\": 5332}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Conversely, method claims protect the steps or processes of making or using an invention, with infringement occurring if someone performs the claimed process, regardless of the equipment used.\", \"from\": 5337, \"to\": 5531, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"method claims\", \"from\": 5349, \"to\": 5362}, {\"ngram\": \"the steps\", \"from\": 5371, \"to\": 5380}, {\"ngram\": \"processes\", \"from\": 5384, \"to\": 5393}, {\"ngram\": \"an invention\", \"from\": 5413, \"to\": 5425}, {\"ngram\": \"infringement\", \"from\": 5432, \"to\": 5444}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 5458, \"to\": 5465}, {\"ngram\": \"the claimed process\", \"from\": 5475, \"to\": 5494}, {\"ngram\": \"the equipment\", \"from\": 5510, \"to\": 5523}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Understanding these differences is crucial for inventors and businesses, as it aids in crafting robust patents that offer comprehensive protection for innovations, whether they are new devices or novel processes.\", \"from\": 5533, \"to\": 5748, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these differences\", \"from\": 5547, \"to\": 5564}, {\"ngram\": \"inventors\", \"from\": 5580, \"to\": 5589}, {\"ngram\": \"businesses\", \"from\": 5594, \"to\": 5604}, {\"ngram\": \"robust patents\", \"from\": 5629, \"to\": 5643}, {\"ngram\": \"comprehensive protection\", \"from\": 5655, \"to\": 5679}, {\"ngram\": \"innovations\", \"from\": 5684, \"to\": 5695}, {\"ngram\": \"new devices\", \"from\": 5714, \"to\": 5725}, {\"ngram\": \"novel processes\", \"from\": 5729, \"to\": 5744}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the competitive arena of patent protection, asserting and/or obtaining an apparatus claim or a method claim can be the difference between a bronze medal and a photo-finish gold.\", \"from\": 5749, \"to\": 5932, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the competitive arena\", \"from\": 5752, \"to\": 5773}, {\"ngram\": \"patent protection\", \"from\": 5777, \"to\": 5794}, {\"ngram\": \"an apparatus claim\", \"from\": 5823, \"to\": 5841}, {\"ngram\": \"a method claim\", \"from\": 5845, \"to\": 5859}, {\"ngram\": \"the difference\", \"from\": 5867, \"to\": 5881}, {\"ngram\": \"a bronze medal\", \"from\": 5890, \"to\": 5904}, {\"ngram\": \"a photo-finish gold\", \"from\": 5909, \"to\": 5928}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The content of this article is intended to provide a general guide to the subject matter.\", \"from\": 5934, \"to\": 6024, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The content\", \"from\": 5934, \"to\": 5945}, {\"ngram\": \"this article\", \"from\": 5949, \"to\": 5961}, {\"ngram\": \"a general guide\", \"from\": 5985, \"to\": 6000}, {\"ngram\": \"the subject matter\", \"from\": 6004, \"to\": 6022}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Specialist advice should be sought about your specific circumstances.\", \"from\": 6025, \"to\": 6095, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Specialist advice\", \"from\": 6025, \"to\": 6042}, {\"ngram\": \"your specific circumstances\", \"from\": 6066, \"to\": 6093}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Connecting Knowledge & People POWERED BYMONDAQ AI \\u00a9 Mondaq\\u00ae Ltd 1994 - 2025.\", \"from\": 6097, \"to\": 6176, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Knowledge & People POWERED\", \"from\": 6108, \"to\": 6134}, {\"ngram\": \"BYMONDAQ AI \\u00a9 Mondaq\\u00ae Ltd\", \"from\": 6135, \"to\": 6160}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All Rights Reserved Mondaq uses cookies on this web